sleAlarmMgr.name: sleAlarmMgr

revisions.description: This MIB module defines the managed objects that support the monitoring of alarms generated by physical entities contained by the system, including chassis, slots, modules, ports, power supplies and fans.

sleAlarmMgr.description: This MIB contains all needed informations about Alarm Manager.

AMTrapState.name: AMTrapState
AMTrapState.description: This status explains whether TRAP status is enabled or disabled. Enable(1) : Alarm Trap State is Enabled. Hence TRAPs will be sent for this. Disable(0) : Alarm Trap State is Disabled. So Alarms won't be notified to user.

AMAlarmGuardTime.name: AMAlarmGuardTime
AMAlarmGuardTime.description: alarm guard time 1~30 (second) 0, no alarm guard time apply

AMAlarmSrc.name: AMAlarmSrc
AMAlarmSrc.description: |type|length|value|type|length|value|.... type (1-byte) : alarm location type length(1-byte) : alarm location value length value (length-bytes) : alarm location value

AlarmStatus.name: AlarmStatus
AlarmStatus.description: This is the status of the alarm. Cleared(0) : Alarm status is cleared Raised(1) : Alarm status is raised. Masked(2) : alarm is suppressed. Disable(3) : Alarm disable Forced-clear(4) : Init alarm Event(5) : Event report Unmasked(6) :Alarm suppression release

AMAlarmReason.name: AMAlarmReason
AMAlarmReason.description: Alarm reason Description string (include location infomatiln)

AMAlarmAco.name: AMAlarmAco
AMAlarmAco.description: ACO control configuration acoOff(1) : buzzer operation enable. acoOn(2) : buzzer operation disable. acoOpr(3) : current buzzer cut.

AMAlarmLed.name: AMAlarmLed
AMAlarmLed.description: LED control configuration ledOff(1) : LED operation disable. ledOn(2) : LED operation enable. ledOpr(3) : current LED off.

sleAMAlarmTrapNeId.name: sleAMAlarmTrapNeId
sleAMAlarmTrapNeId.description: use for NE idendification when alarm(or event) trap system MAC address

sleAMConfigTable.name: sleAMConfigTable
sleAMConfigTable.description: This table is the class Master Alarm table. It gets populated when system init is done. And it contains all the class alarms supported for the device

sleAMConfigAlarmClassId.name: sleAMConfigAlarmClassId
sleAMConfigAlarmClassId.description: Class ID starts from 1 to 65535 for the system. And these IDs are defined by alarm-client

sleAMConfigAlarmId.name: sleAMConfigAlarmId
sleAMConfigAlarmId.description: Alarm ID Alarm ID starts from 1 to 65535 for the system. And these IDs are defined by alarm-client

sleAMConfigAlarmSeverity.name: sleAMConfigAlarmSeverity
sleAMConfigAlarmSeverity.description: Alarm severity: The default severity is pre-defined by each Alarm manager clients critical(1), major(2), minor(3), warning(4), intermediate(5),

sleAMConfigAlarmEnableState.name: sleAMConfigAlarmEnableState
sleAMConfigAlarmEnableState.description: Alarm Trap State. Based on the trap state, the alarm will be notified to NMS. If the TRAP STATE is enabled then the alarm will be notified else wont be notified. enable (1) disabe (0)

sleAMConfigAlarmRaiseGuardTime.name: sleAMConfigAlarmRaiseGuardTime
sleAMConfigAlarmRaiseGuardTime.description: Alarm raise Soaking time. When any alarm is raised, this attribute specifies how much time the alarm should be soaked before notifying to Alarm manager range:1 ~ 30, (if '0', no soaking time)

sleAMConfigAlarmClearGuardTime.name: sleAMConfigAlarmClearGuardTime
sleAMConfigAlarmClearGuardTime.description: Alarm clear Soaking time. When any alarm is cleared, this attribute specifies how much time the alarm should be soaked before notifying to Alarm manager range:1 ~ 30, (if '0', no soaking time)

sleAMConfigAlarmLed.name: sleAMConfigAlarmLed
sleAMConfigAlarmLed.description: Alarm led configuration. Determinde led operate or not, when alarms occur. off(0): led not operate on(1) : led operate

sleAMConfigSpecificId.name: sleAMConfigSpecificId
sleAMConfigSpecificId.description: Alarm Configuration specific ID(4bytes) classId and alarmID are combinded with a specificID * 1st,2nd Bytes - ClassId * 3rd,4th bytes - alarmID

sleAMConfigControlRequest.name: sleAMConfigControlRequest
sleAMConfigControlRequest.description: The configuration commands, and user can configure functions via setting this entry as proper value.

sleAMConfigControlStatus.name: sleAMConfigControlStatus
sleAMConfigControlStatus.description: status of user command. User have to check this value as .busy. or .idle. before do setRequest.

sleAMConfigControlTimer.name: sleAMConfigControlTimer
sleAMConfigControlTimer.description: the wait-time until setRequest end. In case of short-time command, this value is 0

sleAMConfigControlTimeStamp.name: sleAMConfigControlTimeStamp
sleAMConfigControlTimeStamp.description: the time stamp of the last command. (don.t care)

sleAMConfigControlSeverity.name: sleAMConfigControlSeverity
sleAMConfigControlSeverity.description: Alarm Class Severity critical(1), major(2), minor(3), warning(4), ignore(5), default(6)

sleAMConfigControlEnableState.name: sleAMConfigControlEnableState
sleAMConfigControlEnableState.description: Alarm Trap State. Based on the trap state, the alarm will be notified to NMS. If the TRAP STATE is enabled then the alarm will be notified else wont be notified. enable (1) disabe (0)

sleAMConfigControlRaiseGuardTime.name: sleAMConfigControlRaiseGuardTime
sleAMConfigControlRaiseGuardTime.description: Alarm Raise Soaking time. When any alarm is raised, this attribute specifies how much time the alarm should be soaked before notifying to Alarm manager range:1 ~ 30, (if '0', no soaking time)

sleAMConfigControlClearGuardTime.name: sleAMConfigControlClearGuardTime
sleAMConfigControlClearGuardTime.description: Alarm clear Soaking time. When any alarm is cleared, this attribute specifies how much time the alarm should be soaked before notifying to Alarm manager range:1 ~ 30, (if '0', no soaking time)

sleAMConfigControlLed.name: sleAMConfigControlLed
sleAMConfigControlLed.description: Alarm led configuration. Determinde led operate or not, when alarms occur. off(0): led not operate on(1) : led operate
